           <div type="translation" source="bib:Chhom2011_01"><!-- kuch: The term 'slave' should be understood as 'servant'. -->
 	<p n="1-14"><supplied reason="explanation">Ruined</supplied>. <supplied reason="subaudible">Gho</supplied> Khñurṁ, Gho <gap reason="lost"/>, <supplied reason="subaudible">Gho</supplied> Vraḥ <gap reason="lost"/>, Gho Kaṁbhū, Gho Pandan, Gho Śaktibhāva, Gho Vrahma, Gho <gap reason="lost"/>, Gvāl <gap reason="lost"/>, Gvāl <gap reason="lost"/>, Gvāl Saṁ-ap, Gvāl Ājya, Gvāl <gap reason="lost"/> with two babies, Tai Pandan, Tai <gap reason="lost"/>, Tai Vraḥ Niśīya, Tai <gap reason="lost"/>, <supplied reason="subaudible">Tai</supplied> Gandha, Tai Kaṁvau, Tai <gap reason="lost"/> with a baby, Lap <gap reason="lost"/>. Total: thirteen male slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>gho</foreign></supplied>, <gap reason="lost"/> animal keepers <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>gvāl</foreign></supplied>, <gap reason="lost"/> a male slave <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>lap</foreign></supplied>, two boys <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai rat</foreign></supplied>, two baby boys <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>si pau</foreign></supplied>, a baby girl <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai pau</foreign></supplied>; grand total 36.</p>
              <p n="14-22">Village of Kaṁpāy: Si Thkan, Gho Khmau, Gho Vraḥ, Gho Thleṁ, Gho Kanran, Gvāl Kañjaṅ, Tai Kaṁpit, Tai Kandeṅ, Tai Phnos, Tai Cancān, Tai Kan-ak, Tai Thgan with two sons <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>si rat</foreign></supplied>, Tai Jvik with a boy <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>si rat</foreign></supplied>, Lap <gap reason="lost"/> with two <supplied reason="subaudible">children</supplied>; total: 5 male slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>gho</foreign></supplied>, an animal keeper <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>gvāl</foreign></supplied>, seven female slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai</foreign></supplied>, <gap reason="lost"/> male slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>lap</foreign></supplied> <gap reason="lost"/>.</p>
              <p n="22-24">Village of <gap reason="lost"/>, Gho Kaṁpit, Gho <gap reason="lost"/>, <supplied reason="explanation">Ruined</supplied>.</p>
